%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Gen-z%20stepping%20over%20a%20college%20graduation%20cap.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64dfd6e3bd98a6001979c448%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20pandemic%20and%20economic%20uncertainty%2C%20Gen%20Z%20is%20questioning%20whether%20college%20is%20worth%20it.%3Cp%3EChelsea%20Jia%20Feng%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20just%20one%20semester%20for%20Rushil%20Srivastava%20to%20realize%20that%20college%20was%20not%20what%20he%20had%20hoped.%20%26quot%3BAs%20a%20kid%2C%20you%20always%20imagine%20college%20will%20be%20a%20life-changing%20experience%2C%20and%20that%20your%20freshman%20year%20is%20where%20you'll%20get%20a%20chance%20to%20discover%20yourself%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Instead%2C%20he%20was%20forced%20to%20take%20classes%20online%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20COVID%20and%20faced%20a%20campus%20social%20scene%20that%20remained%20fractured.%20The%20computer-science%20major%20wound%20up%20dropping%20out%20of%20UC%20Berkeley%20in%20fall%202021%2C%20only%20a%20few%20months%20after%20he%20had%20enrolled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%20Srivastava%20decided%20to%20launch%20a%20startup%20designed%20to%20help%20job%20seekers%20find%20work.%20Today%2C%20as%20most%20of%20his%20peers%20are%20starting%20their%20senior%20year%20of%20college%2C%20he's%20got%20more%20than%20%241%20million%20in%20venture-capital%20funding.%C2%A0%20%26quot%3BMost%20of%20my%20friends%20are%20just%20now%20finally%20getting%20adjusted%2C%20some%20better%20than%20others%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20now%2020-year-old%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20world%20is%20rapidly%20evolving%20%E2%80%94%20and%20so%20is%20the%20college%20experience.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ESrivastava%20is%20one%20of%20a%20soaring%20number%20of%20Gen%20Zers%20who%20has%20decided%20to%20skip%20college%20altogether.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weforum.org%2Fagenda%2F2023%2F01%2Fus-college-enrolment-is-dropping-can-this-be-reversed-davos23%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFour%20million%20fewer%3C%2Fa%3E%20teenagers%20enrolled%20at%20a%20college%20in%202022%20than%20in%202012.%20For%20many%2C%20the%20price%20tag%20has%20simply%20grown%20too%20exorbitant%20to%20justify%20the%20cost.%20From%202010%20to%202022%2C%20college%20tuition%20rose%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feducationdata.org%2Fcollege-tuition-inflation-rate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaverage%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%2012%25%20a%20year%2C%20while%20overall%20inflation%20only%20increased%20an%20average%20of%202.6%25%20each%20year.%20Today%20it%20costs%20at%20least%20%24104%2C108%20on%20average%20to%20attend%20four%20years%20of%20public%20university%20%E2%80%94%20and%20%24223%2C360%20for%20a%20private%20university.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20salaries%20students%20can%20expect%20to%20earn%20after%20graduation%20haven't%20kept%20up%20with%20the%20cost%20of%20college.%20A%202019%20report%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fsocial-trends%2F2019%2F02%2F14%2Fmillennial-life-how-young-adulthood-today-compares-with-prior-generations-2%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPew%20Research%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20earnings%20for%20young%20college-educated%20workers%20had%20remained%20mostly%20flat%20over%20the%20past%2050%20years.%20Four%20years%20after%20graduating%2C%20according%20to%20recent%20data%20from%20the%20Higher%20Education%20Authority%2C%20a%20third%20of%20students%20earn%20less%20than%20%2440%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20lower%20than%20the%20average%20salary%20of%20%2444%2C356%20that%20workers%20with%20only%20a%20high-school%20diploma%20earn.%20Factor%20in%20the%20average%20student%20debt%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feducationdata.org%2Faverage-student-loan-debt%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2433%2C500%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20college%20graduates%20owe%20after%20they%20leave%20school%2C%20and%20many%20graduates%20will%20spend%20years%20catching%20up%20with%20their%20degree-less%20counterparts.%20This%20student-debt-driven%20financial%20hole%20is%20leaving%20more%20young%20graduates%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Fideas%2Farchive%2F2020%2F01%2Fcollege-wealth-premium-collapsed%2F604579%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elower%20net%20worth%20than%20previous%20generations%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EThe%20focus%20now%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20so%20much%20uncertainty%20in%20the%20economy%2C%20is%20on%20using%20college%20to%20prepare%20for%20a%20single%2C%20overriding%20goal%3A%20getting%20a%20good%20job.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20widening%20gap%20between%20the%20value%20and%20the%20cost%20of%20college%20has%20started%20to%20shift%20Gen%20Z's%20attitude%20toward%20higher%20education.%20A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpro.morningconsult.com%2Fanalysis%2Fmost-trusted-universities-gaps-public-trust%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2022%20survey%20by%20Morning%20Consult%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%2041%25%20of%20Gen%20Zers%20said%20they%20%26quot%3Btend%20to%20trust%20US%20colleges%20and%20universities%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lowest%20percentage%20of%20any%20generation.%20It's%20a%20significant%20shift%20from%20when%20millennials%20were%20in%20their%20shoes%20a%20decade%20ago%3A%20A%202014%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fsocial-trends%2F2014%2F02%2F11%2Fchapter-2-public-views-on-the-value-of-education%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPew%20Research%3C%2Fa%3E%20survey%20found%20that%2063%25%20of%20millennials%20valued%20a%20college%20education%20or%20planned%20to%20get%20one.%20And%20of%20those%20who%20graduated%2C%2041%25%20of%20that%20cohort%20considered%20their%20schooling%20%26quot%3Bvery%20useful%26quot%3B%20in%20readying%20them%20to%20enter%20the%20workforce%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20compared%20to%2045%25%20of%20Gen%20Xers%20and%2047%25%20of%20boomers%20who%20felt%20the%20same.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20Gen%20Zers%20who%20do%20decide%20to%20attend%20college%20enter%20with%20a%20whole%20new%20set%20of%20priorities.%20They're%20not%20as%20interested%20in%20the%20typical%20%26quot%3Bcollege%20experience%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20whiling%20away%20four%20years%20rooming%20with%20friends%20and%20drinking%20at%20frat%20parties.%20College%20today%20is%20simply%20too%20expensive%20for%20fun%20and%20games.%20And%20many%20students%20are%20no%20longer%20drawn%20by%20the%20traditional%20mission%20of%20a%20liberal-arts%20education%3A%20to%20foster%20critical%20thinking%20and%20informed%20discourse.%20The%20focus%20now%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20so%20much%20uncertainty%20in%20the%20economy%2C%20is%20on%20using%20college%20to%20prepare%20for%20a%20single%2C%20overriding%20goal%3A%20getting%20a%20good%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Nora%20Taets%20enrolled%20at%20Iowa%20State%20University%20two%20years%20ago%2C%20she%20started%20off%20with%20a%20major%20in%20entrepreneurship%20and%20a%20minor%20in%20psychology%20because%20it%20sounded%20like%20a%20%26quot%3Bfun%20idea.%26quot%3B%20But%20when%20she%20learned%20that%20her%20major%20could%20make%20her%20less%20attractive%20to%20future%20employers%20%E2%80%94%20because%20they%20might%20think%20she'd%20%26quot%3Bgo%20to%20their%20company%20and%20take%20all%20of%20their%20ideas%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20she%20shifted%20to%20marketing.%20%26quot%3BBy%20switching%2C%20this%20will%20be%20a%20way%20better%20way%20to%20lead%20to%20jobs%20in%20the%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20single-minded%20focus%20on%20jobs%20is%20transforming%20what%20colleges%20actually%20teach.%20Degrees%20that%20lead%20to%20better-paying%20careers%20%E2%80%94%20computer%20science%2C%20engineering%2C%20business%2C%20and%20health%20science%20%E2%80%94%20are%20soaring%20in%20popularity.%20At%20UC%20Berkeley%2C%20computer%20science%20is%20now%20the%20most%20popular%20major%20%E2%80%94%20up%20from%20seventh%20place%20in%202014.%20In%20response%20to%20demand%2C%20the%20university%20recently%20unveiled%20its%20first%20new%20college%20in%20more%20than%20half%20a%20century%3A%20the%20College%20of%20Computing%2C%20Data%20Science%2C%20and%20Society.%20Data%20science%2C%20a%20degree%20established%20only%20five%20years%20ago%2C%20is%20now%20the%20third-most-popular%20degree%20the%20university%20offers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStudents%20are%20increasingly%20drawn%20to%20subjects%20like%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20data%20science%2C%20business%20analytics%2C%20and%20social%20media%2C%26quot%3B%20James%20Connor%2C%20the%20dean%20of%20the%20School%20of%20Business%20and%20Information%20Technology%20at%20San%20Francisco%20Bay%20University%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20surge%20reflects%20their%20understanding%20of%20these%20subjects'%20importance%20for%20career%20competitiveness%20and%20longevity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EThe%20pandemic%20forced%20students%20to%20think%20broadly%20about%20their%20lives%20and%20careers.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EStudents%20are%20also%20devoting%20their%20free%20time%20to%20maximizing%20their%20career%20prospects.%20They%20take%20workshops%20to%20better%20understand%20the%20current%20economic%20situation%3B%20they%20enroll%20in%20additional%20courses%20online%20to%20complete%20their%20degrees%20faster%3B%20and%20they%20constantly%20compare%20notes%20on%20the%20job%20market.%20%26quot%3BOne%20may%20still%20play%20a%20game%20of%20Ping-Pong%20in%20the%20open%20room%2C%26quot%3B%20Connor%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20the%20discussions%20of%20those%20watching%20on%20the%20sidelines%20are%20very%20different.%26quot%3B%20Instead%20of%20talking%20about%20%26quot%3Blocal%20leisure%20activities%20around%20San%20Francisco%20and%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20they%20did%20four%20years%20ago%2C%20he%20said%2C%20they're%20now%20more%20likely%20to%20discuss%20whether%20they%20made%20a%20mistake%20in%20choosing%20computer%20science%20given%20the%20rise%20in%20tech%20layoffs%20or%20whether%20they%20should%20get%20an%20MBA%20to%20avoid%20the%20job%20market%20until%20fears%20of%20a%20recession%20have%20passed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20questions%20would%20have%20been%20atypical%20before%20COVID%2C%20but%20now%20they%20are%20the%20norm%2C%26quot%3B%20Connor%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20pandemic%20forced%20students%20to%20think%20broadly%20about%20their%20lives%20and%20careers%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20in%20a%20long-term%20way.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20majors%20in%20computer%20science%20and%20engineering%20have%20soared%2C%20those%20in%20the%20humanities%20have%20plummeted.%20Last%20year%2C%20only%207%25%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fmagazine%2F2023%2F03%2F06%2Fthe-end-of-the-english-major%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHarvard%3C%2Fa%3E%20freshmen%20planned%20to%20major%20in%20the%20humanities%20%E2%80%94%20down%20from%2020%25%20a%20decade%20earlier%20and%20almost%2030%25%20in%20the%201970s.%20In%20February%2C%20Marymount%20University%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Feducation%2F2023%2F02%2F24%2Fmarymount-university-humanities-majors-eliminated%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20drop%20nine%20liberal-arts%20majors%2C%20including%20English%2C%20history%2C%20and%20philosophy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERichard%20Saller%2C%20a%20classics%20professor%20at%20Stanford%20University%2C%20has%20watched%20with%20concern%20as%20the%20value%20of%20the%20humanities%20in%20the%20broader%20culture%20has%20been%20%26quot%3Bdiluted.%26quot%3B%20While%20he's%20%26quot%3Bnot%20inclined%20to%20make%20a%20dire%20prediction%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20has%20noticed%20that%20such%20subjects%20are%20increasingly%20being%20studied%20only%20by%20those%20who%20can%20afford%20the%20prospect%20of%20a%20lower-paying%20career.%20%26quot%3BThough%20it%20pains%20me%20to%20say%20this%2C%20it%20is%20true%20that%20study%20of%20literature%20and%20other%20forms%20of%20the%20humanities%20has%20been%20something%20that%20has%20been%20more%20popular%20among%20students%20who%20don't%20have%20an%20immediate%20need%20to%20generate%20an%20income%20after%20graduation%2C%26quot%3B%20Saller%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20who%20were%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20college%20when%20COVID%20hit%20bore%20the%20brunt%20of%20the%20changes%20to%20higher%20education.%20Meghan%20Reinhold%2C%20now%2025%2C%20recalled%20%26quot%3Bcrying%20myself%20to%20sleep%26quot%3B%20when%20she%20was%20sent%20home%20from%20campus%20in%20March%202020.%20What%20%26quot%3Bfirst%20seemed%20exciting%2C%20like%20when%20you%20miss%20school%20for%20a%20snow%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20turned%20into%20years%20at%20home%2C%20technological%20issues%20that%20disrupted%20her%20ability%20to%20access%20and%20hand%20in%20assignments%20on%20time%2C%20and%20a%20deeply%20secluded%20existence.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20became%20more%20and%20more%20disconnected%20from%20anyone%20at%20school%2C%20including%20my%20professors%2C%26quot%3B%20recalled%20Reinhold%2C%20who%20majored%20in%20psychology.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20just%20staring%20into%20a%20screen%2C%20and%20it%20didn't%20feel%20like%20I%20was%20in%20college%20anymore.%26quot%3B%20She%20suffered%20from%20%26quot%3Boverwhelming%20anxiety%20and%20frequent%20panic%20attacks%2C%26quot%3B%20became%20addicted%20to%20nicotine%2C%20and%20barely%20ate%2C%20she%20said.%20And%20since%20graduating%2C%20she%20has%20struggled%20to%20find%20a%20job.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20already%20feel%20so%20burned%20out%20from%20just%20trying%20to%20finish%20college%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20I%20haven't%20even%20started%20my%20life%20yet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20online%20classes%20initially%20destroyed%20the%20college%20experience%20for%20many%20students%2C%20some%20are%20now%20opting%20for%20remote%20learning%20over%20campus%20life%20as%20a%20way%20to%20save%20money.%20Prior%20to%20COVID%2C%20around%20a%20third%20of%20university%20teaching%20took%20place%20online%2C%20either%20via%20prerecorded%20lectures%2C%20video%20tutorials%2C%20or%20digitized%20reading%20material.%20Now%2C%20some%20schools%20have%20switched%20to%20online%20only%2C%20while%20others%20are%20capitalizing%20on%20the%20current%20trend%20by%20launching%20business%20programs%20that%20are%20entirely%20virtual.%20In%202011%2C%20300%2C000%20students%20were%20enrolled%20in%20massive%20open%20online%20courses%2C%20or%20MOOCs%2C%20which%20offer%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20courses%20for%20free.%20By%202021%2C%20the%20number%20had%20soared%20to%20220%20million.%20Students%20still%20want%20a%20college%20degree.%20They%20just%20want%20to%20get%20it%20faster%20%E2%80%94%20and%20cheaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20young%20students%2C%20though%2C%20college%20hasn't%20changed%20much.%20Mar%C3%ADa%20Gorgojo%2C%2019%2C%20described%20her%20first%20year%20in%20biomedical%20engineering%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20very%20positive%20and%20enlightening%20experience%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20one%20that%20has%20made%20her%20confident%20in%20her%20choices.%20Regardless%20of%20majors%2C%20she%20said%2C%20college%20life%20remains%20unchanged%20from%20her%20father's%20generation%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20study%2C%20you%20sometimes%20loathe%20your%20professors%2C%20or%20even%20question%20why%20you%20started%20this%20degree%2C%20you%20meet%20new%20people%20and%20you%20realize%20they%20are%20all%20equally%20as%20lost%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20essence%20of%20the%20university%20experience%20remains%20intact.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20other%20members%20of%20Gen%20Z%20are%20taking%20a%20hard%20look%20at%20the%20%26quot%3Bessence%26quot%3B%20of%20college.%20Srivastava%2C%20the%20Berkeley%20dropout%2C%20thinks%20that%20the%20prospect%20of%20reinventing%20what%20higher%20education%20looks%20like%20appeals%20to%20Gen%20Z%2C%20a%20group%20%26quot%3Bknown%20for%20challenging%20the%20status%20quo%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Their%20changing%20views%20%26quot%3Bwill%20fuel%20the%20drive%20for%20innovative%2C%20value-driven%20alternatives%20to%20college.%26quot%3B%20Those%20alternatives%20take%20many%20forms.%20Schools%20like%20Miami%20University%20of%20Ohio%20and%20Arizona%20State%20now%20allow%20honors%20students%20to%20piece%20together%20majors%20of%20their%20own%20design%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20while%20some%20skilled-trade%20programs%20have%20experienced%20a%2040%25%20spike%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2022%2F03%2F20%2F1087766188%2Fskilled-trade-programs-are-booming-after-college-enrollment-dropped-in-the-pande%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eenrollment%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Srivastava%20may%20have%20missed%20out%20on%20the%20tug-of-war%20with%20professors%20and%20campus%20life%2C%20he%20doesn't%20regret%20his%20decision%20to%20be%20a%20student%20of%20the%20world.%20%26quot%3BThe%20experience%20and%20knowledge%20I%20have%20accumulated%20is%20invaluable%20and%20not%20taught%20in%20any%20classrooms%20or%20lecture%20hall%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BEvery%20day%20is%20a%20new%20exciting%20challenge%2C%20and%20I%20am%20learning%20more%20about%20myself%20on%20a%20daily%20basis.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fcharlotte-lytton%5C%22%3ECharlotte%20Lytton%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20journalist%20based%20in%20London.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%