E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESheryl%20Sandberg%20was%20born%20on%20August%2028%2C%201969%2C%20in%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%20Her%20father%20was%20an%20ophthalmologist%20and%20her%20mother%20taught%20French%20at%20a%20local%20college%2C%20according%20to%20the%20New%20Yorker.%20She%20has%20two%20younger%20siblings%3A%20a%20brother%20named%20David%20and%20a%20sister%20named%20Michelle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20family%20moved%20to%20North%20Miami%20Beach%20when%20Sheryl%20was%202%20years%20old%2C%20the%20New%20Yorker%20reported.%20Her%20parents%20helped%20create%20the%20South%20Florida%20Conference%20on%20Soviet%20Jewry%20and%20turned%20their%20home%20into%20a%20safe%20haven%20for%20Soviet%20Jews%20looking%20to%20escape%20anti-Semitism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESandberg%20always%20shone%20in%20school%2C%20and%20was%20in%20the%20National%20Honor%20Society.%20%26quot%3BIn%20public%20schools%2C%20for%20a%20girl%20to%20be%20smart%20was%20not%20good%20for%20your%20social%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20her%20mother%2C%20Adele%2C%20told%20The%20New%20Yorker.%20She%20also%20taught%20aerobics%20while%20in%20high%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESandberg%20attended%20Harvard%20University%2C%20where%20she%20majored%20in%20economics.%20She%20researched%20with%20future%20US%20Treasury%20Secretary%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flarry-summers-paul-krugman-jim-bianco-inflation-chart-crime-2023-8%5C%22%3ELarry%20Summers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20would%20serve%20as%20an%20important%20mentor%20for%20Sandberg%20in%20the%20beginning%20phases%20of%20her%20career.%20Summers%20served%20as%20her%20thesis%20advisor%2C%20then%20hired%20her%20to%20work%20for%20him%20at%20the%20World%20Bank%20after%20she%20graduated%20in%201991.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESandberg%20stayed%20at%20the%20World%20Bank%20for%20a%20year%2C%20during%20which%20she%20traveled%20to%20India%20to%20help%20curb%20the%20spread%20of%20leprosy.%20She%20then%20returned%20to%20Harvard%20to%20get%20an%20MBA%2C%20and%20worked%20for%20a%20year%20at%20the%20global%20consulting%20firm%20McKinsey%20%26amp%3B%20Company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESandberg%20wrote%20in%20Cosmopolitan%20that%20her%20parents%20instilled%20in%20her%20that%20the%20time%20to%20find%20a%20man%20was%20in%20college%2C%20because%20%26quot%3Bthe%20good%20ones%20go%20young.%26quot%3B%20Sandberg%20married%20her%20first%20husbnad%2C%20a%20businessman%20named%20Brian%20Kraff%2C%20at%20age%2024%2C%20but%20they%20got%20divorced%20after%20only%20a%20year.%20She%20said%20she%20was%20nervous%20her%20divorce%20would%20prevent%20her%20from%20ever%20meeting%20someone%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESandberg%20followed%20Summers%20to%20D.C.%20to%20work%20for%20him%2C%20and%20eventually%20became%20his%20chief%20of%20staff%20when%20he%20was%20named%20Treasury%20secretary%20in%201999.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20after%20the%20Democrats%20lost%20the%202000%20election%2C%20Sandberg%20decided%20to%20move%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsilicon-valley-history-technology-industry-animated-timeline-video-2017-5%5C%22%3ESilicon%20Valley%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20join%20the%20booming%20tech%20industry%2C%20the%20New%20Yorker%20reported.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20Google%20was%20a%20small%20company%20with%20less%20than%20300%20people%20that%20wasn't%20making%20a%20profit.%20However%2C%20she%20found%20the%20company%20had%20an%20attractive%20mission%3A%20%26quot%3Bto%20make%20the%20world's%20information%20freely%20available.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESandberg%20joined%20Google%20as%20the%20business-unit%20general%20manager%20in%202001%20and%20took%20over%20the%20company's%20ad%20program%2C%20which%20had%20four%20people%20working%20on%20it%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22702%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dave%20Goldberg%20and%20Sheryl%20Sandberg%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5988c510875433421831c2a0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22527%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESheryl%20Sandberg%20with%20her%20second%20husband