-khans-wife-bushra-bibi-moves-lahore-court-against-her-possible-arrest%2Farticleshow%2F103378673.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fpakistan%2Fpakistan-imran-khans-wife-bushra-bibi-moves-lahore-court-against-her-possible-arrest%2Famp_articleshow%2F103378673.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fpakistan%2Fpakistan-imran-khans-wife-bushra-bibi-moves-lahore-court-against-her-possible-arrest%2Famp_articleshow%2F103378673.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Article%20370%3A%20As%20SC%20Asks%20Petitioner%20to%20Swear%20Allegiance%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20Sovereignty%2C%20Constitution%20Itself%20Is%20on%20Trial%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3ETime%20and%20again%2C%20high%20courts%20and%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20have%20observed%20that%20it%20is%20unethical%20and%20illegal%20for%20lawyers%20to%20pass%20resolutions%20against%20representing%20accused%20persons%20in%20court.%20In%202020%2C%20when%20some%20local%20bar%20associations%20in%20Karnataka%20had%20objected%20to%20four%20students%20arrested%20for%20sedition%20being%20defended%20in%20court%2C%20the%20Karnataka%20high%20court%20intervened%20and%20sought%20the%20withdrawal%20of%20such%20resolutions.%20In%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1355688%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EA.S.%20Mohammed%20Rafi%20v%20State%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20deprecated%20the%20practice%20of%20advocates%20collectively%20refusing%20to%20take%20up%20the%20defence%20of%20those%20accused%20of%20certain%20offences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20Constitution%20Bench%20hearing%20the%20challenges%20to%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%20reiterated%20that%20it%20is%20duty-bound%20to%20hear%20submissions%20of%20every%20petitioner%20who%20comes%20to%20the%20court.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20had%20people%20from%20across%20the%20political%20spectrum%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20it%20is%20welcome%2C%E2%80%9D%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20the%20bench%20said%20it%20would%20hear%20senior%20counsel%20Kapil%20Sibal%2C%20appearing%20for%20National%20Conference%20leader%20and%20MP%20Mohammad%20Akbar%20Lone%2C%20who%20is%20the%20lead%20petitioner%20in%20the%20case.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20will%20hear%20you%20for%20Mr%20Lone%20as%20well.%20There%E2%80%99s%20no%20difficulty.%20He%20has%20come%20to%20our%20court%2C%20we%20are%20duty-bound%20to%20hear%20his%20submissions%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20told%20Sibal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20bench%E2%80%99s%20insistence%20that%20Sibal%20should%20ask%20Lone%20to%20file%20an%20affidavit%20that%20he%20unconditionally%20accepts%20that%20J%26amp%3BK%20is%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20India%20and%20that%20he%20abides%20by%20and%20owes%20allegiance%20to%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%20is%20likely%20to%20bring%20its%20initial%20declaration%20%E2%80%93%20that%20it%20would%20hear%20everyone%20who%20comes%20to%20the%20court%20%E2%80%93%20into%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20controversy%20arose%20when%20a%20counsel%2C%20representing%20a%20Kashmiri%20Pandits%E2%80%99%20organisation%20%E2%80%98Roots%20in%20Kashmir%E2%80%99%2C%20stated%20that%20Lone%20had%20made%20pro-Pakistan%20slogans%20in%20the%20state%20assembly.%C2%A0%20Other%20senior%20counsel%20including%20Solicitor%20General%20Tushar%20Mehta%20insisted%20that%20Lone%20should%20file%20an%20affidavit%20in%20the%20court%20asserting%20that%20he%20owed%20allegiance%20to%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%20and%20opposed%20secessionist%20forces%20and%20terrorism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECounsel%20for%20other%20respondents%20and%20intervenors%20soon%20urged%20Lone%20to%20apologise%20and%20asked%20the%20court%20to%20take%20his%20submissions%20on%20record%20only%20if%20he%20expresses%20remorse%20for%20his%20statements%2C%20and%20specifically%20opposes%20secessionist%20activities%20and%20terrorism%20by%20Pakistan%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20observations%20by%20counsel%20made%20interesting%20reading.%20Senior%20advocate%20Rakesh%20Dwivedi%2C%20appearing%20for%20an%20intervenor%20supporting%20the%20Union%20government%2C%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CIf%20he%20is%20invoking%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%2C%20then%20he%20can%E2%80%99t%20stand%20outside%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMehta%20warned%20that%20Lone%E2%80%99s%20lack%20of%20remorse%20for%20his%20statement%2C%20if%20ignored%2C%20might%20encourage%20others%2C%20and%20the%20efforts%20of%20the%20nation%20to%20bring%20in%20normalcy%20might%20be%20affected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESibal%2C%20however%2C%20objected%20to%20derailing%20his%20constitutional%20arguments%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20what%20his%20client%20might%20have%20said%20in%20a%20different%20context.%20Sibal%20claimed%20he%20was%20not%20responsible%20for%20what%20his%20client%20might%20have%20said%2C%20and%20that%20he%20was%20not%20even%20concerned%20with%20it.%20%E2%80%9CEveryone%20has%20fundamental%20rights%20in%20this%20country%20including%20those%20who%20on%20the%20streets%20you%20vilify%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sibal%20replied%20to%20the%20vociferous%20demand%20from%20the%20respondents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESibal%E2%80%99s%20reiteration%20of%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20commitment%20to%20J%26amp%3BK%20being%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20India%2C%20and%20Lone%E2%80%99s%20oath%20as%20an%20MP%20owing%20allegiance%20to%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%2C%20failed%20to%20convince%20the%20bench%2C%20which%20suggested%20that%20Lone%20could%20file%20an%20affidavit%20as%20a%20way%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAttorney%20General%20R.%20Venkataramani%20submitted%20that%20a%20person%20seeking%20to%20enforce%20his%20fundamental%20rights%20should%20have%20faith%20in%20the%20Constitution%20%E2%80%93%20a%20remark%20which%20reminded%20observers%20of%20what%20human%20rights%20defender%2C%20the%20late%20K.G.%20Kannabiran%2C%20had%20told%20an%20interviewer%20several%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKannabiran%20told%20the%20interviewer%20that%20he%20was%20once%20asked%20by%20a%20judge%20why%20he%2C%20as%20an%20advocate%2C%20seeks%20to%20defend%20those%20who%20believe%20in%20overthrowing%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%2C%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20rights%20guaranteed%20by%20the%20same%20Constitution.%C2%A0%20Kannabiran%20replied%20to%20the%20judge%20thus%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20these%20cases%2C%20it%20is%20not%20the%20accused%20who%20is%20on%20trial%2C%20but%20the%20Constitution%20itself%20is%20on%20trial%2C%20as%20it%20cannot%20deny%20justice%20to%20a%20person%20who%20does%20not%20believe%20in%20it.%20Notwithstanding%20their%20values%2C%20the%20accused%20are%20entitled%20to%20protection%20under%20the%20Constitution.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%E2%80%99s%20insistence%20on%20an%20affidavit%20by%20Lone%20expressing%20his%20allegiance%20to%20the%20Constitution%20and%20Indian%20sovereignty%20came%20close%20to%20a%20%E2%80%9Cwe-they%E2%80%9D%20divide%20which%20characterises%20much%20of%20the%20discourse%20on%20J%26amp%3BK.%20Sibal%20put%20it%20succinctly%3A%20%E2%80%9CTo%20say%20that%20you%20must%20respect%20our%20sentiments%20as%20if%20they%E2%80%99re%20somebody%20else%20itself%20is%20creating%20a%20kind%20of%20chasm%20it%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20creating.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESibal%20was%20referring%20to%20the%20argument%20by%20one%20counsel%20(among%20the%20respondents)%20that%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20respect%20the%20sentiments%20of%20people%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20but%20they%20must%20also%20respect%20our%20sentiments%E2%80%9D.%20Sibal%20equated%20such%20an%20argument%20to%20an%20emotive%2C%20majoritarian%20interpretation%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESibal%2C%20however%2C%20agreed%20with%20the%20bench%20that%20Lone%20may%20be%20asked%20to%20file%20an%20affidavit%20explaining%20the%20circumstances%20of%20his%20alleged%20slogans%20raised%20in%20the%20assembly%20in%20support%20of%20Pakistan.%20On%20the%20face%20of%20it%2C%20raising%20slogans%20in%20support%20of%20Pakistan%20%E2%80%93%20without%20defending%20its%20overt%20or%20covert%20support%20to%20terrorism%20or%20secessionism%20%E2%80%93%20may%20not%20disqualify%20Lone%20from%20seeking%20legal%20remedies%20from%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaving%20taken%20oath%20as%20an%20MP%2C%20Lone%20may%20not%20find%20it%20a%20problem%20to%20reiterate%2C%20as%20a%20petitioner%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20his%20allegiance%20to%20the%20Constitution%E2%80%99s%20ideals%20of%20fraternity%20and%20social%20justice%20and%20J%26amp%3BK%20being%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20India.%C2%A0%20It%20is%20obvious%2C%20however%2C%20that%20his%20professed%20allegiance%20to%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%20and%20its%20sovereignty%20cannot%20come%20in%20the%20way%20of%20his%20challenging%20provisions%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20or%20its%20amendments%2C%20which%20he%20deems%20as%20discriminatory%20to%20the%20people%20of%20J%26amp%3BK.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20hearing%20is%20likely%20to%20conclude%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20September%205.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693890490000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Farticle-370-as-sc-asks-petitioner-to-swear-allegiance-to-indias-sovereignty-constitution-itself-is-on-trial%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Constitution%20Bench%E2%80%99s%20instant%20decision%20%E2%80%93%20on%20a%20plea%20by%20Solicitor%20General%20Tushar%20Mehta%20%E2%80%93%20to%20seek%20an%20affidavit%20from%20Lok%20Sabha%20MP%20Akbar%20Lone%2C%20who%20is%20a%20lead%20petitioner%20in%20the%20case%2C%20declaring%20his%20allegiance%20to%20the%20Indian%20sovereignty%2C%20