20as%20a%20monolithic%20indigenous%20religion.%20He%20attempts%20to%20emphasise%20a%20certain%20essentialist%20view%20of%20Hinduism%20in%20these%20lectures.%20Such%20an%20assumption%20needs%20to%20be%20examined%20in%20the%20light%20of%20recent%20scholarship%20on%20Hinduism.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERadhakrishnan%20was%20conscious%20of%20the%20plurality%20of%20practices%20and%20beliefs%20of%20different%20faiths%20%E2%80%93%20at%20times%20leading%20to%20conflict%20%E2%80%93%20that%20prevailed%20in%20this%20land%20throughout%20its%20history%20but%20his%20anxiety%20to%20see%20a%20unity%20is%20revealed%20by%20his%20continuous%20emphasis%20about%20a%20certain%20spirit%20that%20binds%20the%20religious%20experiences%20of%20the%20people%20of%20this%20land.%20Such%20a%20bond%20is%20captured%20and%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.in%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D2LzRkWABC6sC%26printsec%3Dfrontcover%26dq%3DRobert%2BMinor%2BRadhakrishnan%26hl%3Den%26newbks%3D1%26newbks_redir%3D0%26sa%3DX%26redir_esc%3Dy%23v%3Donepage%26q%3Dconceptualized%252520in%252520terms%26f%3Dfalse%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Econceptualised%20in%20terms%20of%20one%20category%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20in%20the%20words%20of%20Robert%20N.%20Minor%2C%20namely%20the%20category%20of%20Hindus.%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHaving%20spoken%20of%20diversity%20in%20the%20beginning%2C%20he%20then%20goes%20on%20to%20expatiate%20on%20the%20one%20stereotypical%20idea%20of%20Hinduism%20rooted%20in%20Vedas.%20The%20Vedas%2C%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EUpanishads%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBhagvad%20Gita%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20are%2C%20for%20him%2C%20the%20sacred%20texts%20of%20the%20Hindus.%20He%20holds%20up%20such%20an%20essence%20of%20monolithic%20Hinduism%20by%20his%20rhetoric%20of%20spirituality%20and%20mysticism%20that%2C%20to%20a%20great%20extent%2C%20makes%20his%20views%20obfuscated%20and%20lacking%20in%20analysis.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20presents%20the%20idea%20of%20Hinduism%20with%20the%20underlying%20assumption%20that%20it%20is%20a%20monolithic%20religious%20entity%20but%20with%20the%20capacity%20to%20%E2%80%9Cabsorb%E2%80%9D%20multiple%20beliefs%2C%20customs%20and%20ideas.%20But%20this%20variety%2C%20for%20him%2C%20instead%20of%20undermining%20the%20idea%20of%20monolithic%20Hinduism%2C%20is%20what%20makes%20it%20so%20vibrant%20(perhaps%20this%20idea%20is%20often%20eulogised%2C%20in%20later%20discourses%20by%20others%2C%20by%20the%20phrase%20%E2%80%98unity%20in%20diversity%E2%80%99).%20Further%2C%20he%20portrays%20this%20capacity%20to%20absorb%20as%20one%20of%20growth%2C%20progress%20and%20conservation%20in%20the%20thoughts%20of%20the%20Hindus%20but%20rooted%20in%20Vedanta.%20Without%20making%20an%20argument%20for%20the%20existence%20of%20the%20monolithic%20idea%20of%20Hinduism%20he%20presupposes%20this%20as%20something%20that%20is%20given.%20What%20underlies%20the%20unity%20of%20the%20Hindu%20thought%20is%20the%20spiritual%20oneness%20that%20he%20so%20passionately%20appeals%20to.%20He%20thus%20attempts%20to%20reconcile%2C%20rather%20unconvincingly%2C%20the%20pronounced%20diversity%20of%20multiple%20faiths%2C%20which%20evolved%20in%20the%20course%20of%20the%20history%20of%20this%20land%2C%20and%20a%20hammered%20unity%20conceptualised%20under%20the%20category%20of%20Hinduism.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERadhakrishnan%E2%80%99s%20focus%20is%20on%20the%20aspect%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Espirituality%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20his%20grand%20discussion%20on%20Hinduism.%20By%20virtue%20of%20combining%20the%20right%20measure%20of%20seeming%20profundity%20and%20concealed%20ambiguity%20in%20the%20use%20of%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98spirituality%E2%80%99%2C%20throughout%20his%20discourse%2C%20he%20attempts%20to%20pull%20together%20the%20diversity%20of%20faiths%20and%20beliefs%20that%20prevailed%20in%20the%20country%20under%20his%20monolithic%20concept%20of%20Hinduism.%20It%20is%20a%20slippery%20and%20nebulous%20term%20that%20succinctly%20conveys%20a%20meaning%20which%20many%20think%20they%20can%20comprehend%20but%20anyone%20could%20read%20any%20meaning%20they%20wished%20with%20a%20feeling%20that%20they%20have%20plumbed%20profound%20depths%20in%20their%20supposed%20comprehension%20of%20this%20term.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%2C%20in%20his%20attempt%20to%20expound%20the%20nature%20of%20spirituality%2C%20with%20rhetorical%20flourish%2C%20harnesses%20the%20slipperiness%20of%20the%20term%20to%20construct%20an%20essentialist%20notion%20of%20monolithic%20Hinduism.%20He%20thus%20presents%2C%20what%20would%20appear%20to%20be%2C%20a%20seemingly%20rich%20discussion%20on%20Hinduism%20to%20any%20lay%20reader.%20Moreover%2C%20a%20point%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20noted%20is%20that%20spirituality%2C%20a%20term%20laden%20with%20obscurity%2C%20is%20a%20modern%20Western%20construct%20that%20Hinduism%20has%20appropriated%20in%20the%2018%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%2019%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20centuries%20through%20the%20Protestant%20missionaries%20and%20Orientalists.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERadhakrishnan%2C%20from%20the%20very%20first%20lecture%2C%20develops%20a%20view%20that%20assumes%20a%20unified%20religion%20(or%20civilisation%20or%20culture)%20called%20Hindu.%20It%20never%20occurred%20to%20him%20to%20examine%20how%20this%20monolithic%20entity%20involved%20a%20process%20of%20invention%20and%20construction%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20colonial%20times%20%E2%80%93%20an%20idea%20that%20was%20taken%20up%20and%20popularised%20by%20Swami%20Vivekananda.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Hindu%20View%20of%20Life%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eis%20replete%20with%20obscure%20expressions%20and%20analogies%20and%20appears%20to%20be%20more%20a%20laudatory%20exposition%20of%20Hinduism%20than%20a%20work%20of%20an%20analytical%20mind.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAn%20analytical%20understanding%20of%20Hinduism%2C%20as%20it%20later%20evolved%20%E2%80%93%20one%20that%20is%20expected%20of%20a%20philosopher%20%E2%80%93%20seems%20missing%20in%20this%20book.%20Gauri%20Viswanathan%2C%20a%20scholar%20at%20Columbia%20University%2C%20well%20captures%20such%20an%20understanding%20of%20modern%20scholarship%2C%20in%20her%20essay%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.in%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DLexraSEgRfIC%26printsec%3Dfrontcover%26source%3Dgbs_ge_summary_r%26cad%3D0%23v%3Dsnippet%26q%3DOne%252520of%252520the%252520most%252520striking%252520advances%26f%3Dfalse%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EColonialism%20and%20the%20Construction%20of%20Hinduism%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20where%20she%20notes%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9COne%20of%20the%20most%20striking%20advances%20in%20modern%20scholarship%20is%20the%20view%20that%20there%20is%20no%20such%20thing%20as%20an%20unbroken%20tradition%20of%20Hinduism%2C%20only%20a%20set%20of%20discrete%20traditions%20and%20practices%20reorganized%20into%20a%20larger%20entity%20called%20%E2%80%98Hinduism%E2%80%99%E2%80%A6%20If%20there%20is%20any%20disagreement%20at%20all%20in%20this%20scholarship%2C%20it%20centres%20on%20whether%20Hinduism%20is%20exclusively%20a%20construct%20of%20western%20scholars%20studying%20India%20or%20of%20anticolonial%20Hindus%20looking%20toward%20the%20systematisation%20of%20disparate%20practices%20as%20a%20means%20of%20recovering%20a%20precolonial%2C%20national%20identity.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIssues%20pertaining%20to%20the%20characterisation%20and%20meaning%20of%20religion%20become%20significant%20in%20this%20context.%20In%20meticulously%20presenting%20how%20the%20meaning%20of%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98religion%E2%80%99%20evolved%20in%20history%2C%20William%20Cantwell%20Smith%20argues%20in%20his%20classic%20work%20on%20religion%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.in%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DPNl1QexhUlIC%26printsec%3Dfrontcover%26source%3Dgbs_ge_summary_r%26cad%3D0%23v%3Donepage%26q%26f%3Dfalse%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Meaning%20and%20End%20of%20Religion%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E(1962)%20that%20religion%20is%20nothing%20but%20a%20constructed%20entity.%20Drawing%20upon%20this%20work%2C%20Richard%20King%2C%20religious%20studies%20scholar%20and%20historian%20of%20ideas%20notes%20(in%20his%20essay%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F3270313%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EOrientalism%20and%20the%20Modern%20Myth%20of%20%E2%80%9CHinduism%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E)%2C%20how%20a%20%E2%80%98myth%20of%20homogeneity%E2%80%99%20is%20created%20in%20fashioning%20the%20meaning%20of%20religion%20as%20a%20systematised%20entity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20%E2%80%9Chighly%20abstract%20and%20univocal%20systems%20of%20thought%E2%80%9D%20is%20imposed%20on%20multifarious%20religious%20experiences%20and%20on%20human%20cultural%20diversity.%20Coming%20specifically%20to%20Hinduism%2C%20King%20notes%20that%20the%20implications%20of%20this%20generalised%20and%20constructed%20view%20of%20religion%20can%20be%20seen%20in%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9CModern%20Myth%20of%20%E2%80%98Hinduism%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D.%20The%20doctrines%20of%20this%20modern%20Hinduism%20is%20sometimes%20referred%20to%20as%20%E2%80%9CNeo-Hinduism%E2%80%9D%20(a%20term%20employed%20by%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FPaul_Hacker_(Indologist)%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EPaul%20Hacker%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20a%20German%20Indologist%2C%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FRobert_Antoine%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ERobert%20Antoine%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20a%20Sanskritist)%2C%20the%20newness%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9CNeo-Hinduism%E2%80%9D%20being%20a%20factor%20of%20Orientalist%20and%20Western%20influence%20on%20the%20study%20of%20religious%20experiences%20of%20the%20people%20of%20India.%20Swami%20Vivekananda%20and%20Radhakrishnan%20are%20counted%20primarily%2C%20among%20others%2C%20as%20being%20associated%20with%20this%20form%20of%20homogenised%20Neo-Hinduism.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERadhakrishnan%E2%80%99s%20exposition%2C%20through%20the%20grandiloquence%20of%20language%2C%20gives%20rise%20to%20a%20view%20of%20a%20culturally%20superior%2C%20monolithic-essentialist%20Hinduism%20that%20is%20home%20grown.%20Such%20grandiloquence%20conceals%20the%20%E2%80%9Cheterogeneity%20of%20Indian%20religiosity%E2%80%9D%20and%20instead%20constructs%20an%20ideological%20and%20hegemonic%20discourse%20that%20best%20supports%2C%20as%20King%20notes%2C%20cultural%20and%20political%20elitism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHis%20constructivist%20presentation%20can%20further%20be%20seen%20as%20espousing%20the%20idea%20of%20Hinduism%20that%20is%20more%20prescriptive%20in%20nature%20(i.e.%20by%20prescribing%20what%20constitutes%20Hinduism)%20rather%20than%20descriptive.%20It%20is%20bound%20to%20be%20prescriptive%20as%20any%20constructivist%20agenda%2C%20particularly%20in%20matters%20of%20faith%2C%20cannot%20be%20descriptive.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESuch%20a%20prescriptive%20view%20of%20Hinduism%20may%20serve%20the%20agenda%20of%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20and%20its%20pro-Hindutva%20adherents%20but%20falls%20far%20short%20of%20the%20standards%20of%20philosophical%20and%20historical%20scholarship.%20Not%20surprisingly%2C%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20thrusts%20that%20very%20monolithic%20and%20hegemonic%20notion%20of%20Hinduism%20across%20the%20country.%20As%20Jawhar%20Sircar%2C%20a%20prominent%20public%20intellectual%20and%20a%20member%20of%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Freligion%2Ftarakeshwars-shiva-how-hindu-politics-has-still-a-lot-of-room-to-negotiate%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eobserves%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20BJP%20just%20does%20not%20appreciate%20that%20in%20different%20corners%20of%20the%20country%2C%20every%20shade%20of%20Hinduism%20and%20every%20cult%20represents%20something%20historic%20to%20its%20supporters.%20The%20party%20comprises%20largely-unthinking%20fatuous%20minds%20that%20obviously%20blunder%20when%20they%20miss%20the%20subtleties%2C%20oversimplify%2C%20or%20view%20the%20world%20from%20their%20narrow%20prisms.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ES.K.%20Arun%20Murthi%20has%20taught%20philosophy%20in%20the%20Humanities%20and%20the%20Social%20Sciences%20department%2C%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Science%20Education%20and%20Research%2C%20Mohali%2C%20Punjab.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693887675000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F05094725%2FUntitled-design-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Freligion%2Fradhakrishnan-hinduism-rss-gita-veda-upanishad%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22His%20monolithic%20view%20of%20Hinduism%20may%20serve%20the%20agenda%20of%20the%20RSS%20and%20its%20pro-Hindutva%20adherents%20but%20falls%20far%20short%20of%20the%20standards%20of%20philosophical%20and%20historical%20scholarship.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Freligion%2Fradhakrishnan-hinduism-rss-gita-veda-upanishad%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Cuba%20uncovers%20human%20trafficking%20for%20Russia's%20war%20in%20Ukraine%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693886602000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fm