en%20preceded%20and%20incited%20by%20hateful%20and%20inflammatory%20speech%20that%20spread%20online%20and%20offline%20to%20justify%20the%20atrocities%20committed%20against%20the%20Kuki%20ethnic%20minority%2C%20particularly%20women%2C%20on%20account%20of%20their%20ethnicity%20and%20religious%20belief%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20experts%20welcomed%20fact-finding%20missions%20conducted%20by%20lawyers%20and%20human%20rights%20activists%20in%20Manipur%2C%20but%20noted%20reports%20that%20such%20initiatives%20were%20being%20responded%20to%20with%20harassment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20such%20fact-finding%20mission%2C%20by%20the%20Editors%E2%80%99%20Guild%20of%20India%20(EGI)%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feditorsguild.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FEGI-report-on-Manipur.pdf%5C%22%3Esubmitted%20its%20findings%20three%20days%20ago%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20only%20for%20the%20Manipur%20police%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fmanipur-police-files-fir-against-editors-guild-fact-finding-team-cites-revoked-sec-66a%5C%22%3Efile%20an%20FIR%20against%20it%20soon%20after%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEGI%E2%80%99s%20report%20had%20criticised%20the%20Manipur%20government%E2%80%99s%20internet%20shutdown%20and%20said%20that%20the%20media%20based%20out%20of%20Imphal%20had%20turned%20into%20%E2%80%9CMeitei%20media%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManipur%20chief%20minister%20N.%20Biren%20Singh%20responded%20to%20the%20report%20and%20accused%20the%20EGI%20of%20%E2%80%9Ctrying%20to%20create%20more%20clashes%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20second%20fact-finding%20team%20that%20has%20seen%20legal%20action%20after%20publishing%20a%20report%20on%20Manipur.%20In%20July%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmanipur-violence-fir-fact-finding-team%5C%22%3Ea%20case%20was%20registered%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20Annie%20Raja%2C%20Nisha%20Siddhu%20and%20Deeksha%20Dwivedi%2C%20who%20were%20part%20of%20the%20National%20Federation%20of%20Indian%20Women%E2%80%99s%20team%20in%20Manipur%20and%20had%20said%20in%20their%20report%20that%20Manipur%20was%20seeing%20%E2%80%9Cstate-sponsored%20violence%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UN%20experts%20also%20expressed%20concern%20over%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20response%20to%20the%20violence%2C%20which%20continues%20to%20rage%20over%20four%20months%20after%20it%20began.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20serious%20concerns%20about%20the%20apparent%20slow%20and%20inadequate%20response%20by%20the%20Government%20of%20India%2C%20including%20law%20enforcement%2C%20to%20stem%20physical%20and%20sexual%20violence%20and%20hate%20speech%20in%20Manipur%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20press%20release%20quoted%20the%20experts%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20observers%20have%20also%20criticised%20the%20Union%20government%20for%20not%20doing%20enough%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20to%20Karan%20Thapar%20for%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20historian%20Ramachandra%20Guha%20said%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fvideo-ramachandra-guha-karan-thapar-narendra-modi-manipur%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cmandatory%20first%20step%20to%20stop%20this%20situation%20slipping%20further%20into%20civil%20war%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20Biren%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20resignation.%20Singh%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.crisisgroup.org%2Fasia%2Fsouth-asia%2Findia%2Fethnic-clashes-roiling-manipur-pose-test-indias-modi%5C%22%3Eviewed%20by%20many%20in%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20Kuki%20community%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20acting%20in%20a%20partisan%20manner%20favourable%20to%20the%20Meitei%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2018%20experts%2C%20most%20of%20whom%20are%20special%20rapporteurs%20working%20with%20the%20UN%20Human%20Rights%20Council%2C%20concluded%20their%20statements%20by%20hoping%20that%20public%20officials%20who%20may%20have%20aided%20and%20abetted%20the%20